The '2007â08 A-League' was the third season of the Australian A-League football
(soccer) competition, won by the Newcastle Jets. Football Federation Australia
hoped to build on the success of the previous two seasons and on the interest
generated by and playing in the 2007 AFC Champions League, and the Socceroos
competing in the 2007 AFC Asian Cup.

Based on their A-League 2006-07 season performances and competed in the 2008 AFC
Champions League, making it two consecutive seasons in the competition for .
Based on the 2007-08 season of the A-League, the Central Coast Mariners and
qualified for the 2009 AFC Champions League, as the competition's Premiers and
Champions respectively.

Changes included: *The , who folded at the conclusion of the 2006-07 season,
were replaced by . *An increase of the
squad size, from 20 to 23 players, increasing the salary cap from A$1.6 million
to A$1.85 million.
